<div type="abstract"><head>Rat an Gabriel Ridler</head><p>Der Rat teilt mit, dass er über das Bürgerrecht keinen offenen Brief ausstellt, sondern bei Bedarf einen "Förderbrief" schreibt, und bittet Ridler, seinem Sohn Anton nach dessen Rückkehr zu sagen, dass er wie andere Bürger zu Nürnberg in der Stadt zu wohnen hat.</p>
</div>
<!--This div could possibly contain the analytic portion of the edition.-->
<div type="linguisticAnalysis"><ab><w join="" lemma="" msd="" part="" pos=""><fLib><f name=" "/></fLib></w></ab></div>
</front>
<body><div type="diplomatic"><pb facs="#facs_200" id="99v"/><!--The following div is the container for the adress lines of the letter.-->
<div type="addressee"><ab facs="#facs_200_r1l9">Gabrielen Rıdler </ab>
</div>
<!-- This div contains the letter itselfs. Additions to the text are contained in <add/> elements, struck text in <hi> elements with the attribute 'strikethrough' set to true. -->
<div type="content"><ab facs="#facs_200_r1l10"><expan>Lıeb<ex>er</ex></expan> her Ridler / Als Jr vns <expan>v<ex>er</ex>ſchr<ex>iben</ex></expan> habt von <expan>ew<ex>r</ex>s</expan> Suns <expan>vveg<ex>en</ex></expan> </ab>
<ab facs="#facs_200_r1l11">Anthoni <expan>Rıdl<ex>er</ex>s</expan> <expan>vnſ<ex>er</ex>s</expan> <expan>Burg<ex>er</ex>s</expan> / vnd begert / daʒ vvir Jm des <expan>vnſ<ex>er</ex>n</expan> </ab>
<ab facs="#facs_200_r1l12"><expan>offen<ex>en</ex></expan> brief <expan>geb<ex>e</ex>n</expan> <expan>ſolt<ex>e</ex>n</expan> / daʒ er <expan>vnſ<ex>er</ex></expan> <expan>B<ex>ur</ex>g<ex>er</ex></expan> ıſt / . <expan>Laſſ<ex>en</ex></expan> wir ew vvıſſen </ab>
<ab facs="#facs_200_r1l13">daʒ vnſer gewonheit nicht ıſt / daʒ wir <expan>dheine<ex>m</ex></expan> <expan>vnſ<ex>er</ex>m</expan> <expan>B<ex>urger</ex></expan> . <expan>darv<ex>m</ex>b</expan> </ab>
<ab facs="#facs_200_r1l14"><expan>offen<ex>en</ex></expan> brief <expan>geb<ex>e</ex>n</expan> / . dann ob <expan>d<ex>er</ex></expan> <expan>eg<ex>enante</ex></expan> ewr Sun ıht haftes </ab>
<ab facs="#facs_200_r1l15">gewünn / wenn das an vns braht würd / ſo <expan>geb<ex>e</ex>n</expan> wir Jm </ab>
<ab facs="#facs_200_r1l16"><expan>g<ex>er</ex>ne</expan> <expan>vnſ<ex>er</ex></expan> fürderbrief als <expan>and<ex>er</ex>n</expan> <expan>vnſ<ex>er</ex>n</expan> <expan>B<ex>ur</ex>g<ex>er</ex>n</expan> / vnd <expan>bitt<ex>e</ex>n</expan> ew </ab>
<ab facs="#facs_200_r1l17">wenn er cʒeland kum / daʒ Jr Jn <expan>vnt<ex>er</ex>weiſet</expan> / daʒ er beÿ vns </ab>
<ab facs="#facs_200_r1l18">wonhaft ſeÿ / als <expan>and<ex>er</ex></expan> <expan>vnſ<ex>er</ex></expan> <expan>B<ex>urger</ex></expan> . vnd wo vvir ew lıeb vnd </ab>
<ab facs="#facs_200_r1l19"><expan>frewntſch<ex>aft</ex></expan> <expan>beweıſ<ex>en</ex></expan> <expan>möht<ex>en</ex></expan> / das <expan>tet<ex>e</ex>n</expan> vvir <expan>allcʒ<ex>eit</ex></expan> <expan>g<ex>er</ex>ne</expan> </ab>
</div>
</div><div type="regularised"><pb facs="#facs_200" id="99v"/><!--The following div is the container for the adress lines of the letter.-->
<div type="addressee">
<ab>Gabrielen Ridler </ab>
</div>
<!-- This div contains the letter itselfs. Additions to the text are contained in <add/> elements, struck text in <hi> elements with the attribute 'strikethrough' set to true. -->
<div type="content">
<ab><expan>Lieb<ex>er</ex></expan> her Ridler, als ir uns
                                <expan>v<ex>er</ex>schr<ex>iben</ex></expan> habt von
                                <expan>ew<ex>r</ex>s</expan> suns <expan>weg<ex>en</ex></expan>,
                        Anthoni <expan>Ridl<ex>er</ex>s</expan>, <expan>uns<ex>er</ex>s</expan>
<expan>burg<ex>er</ex>s</expan>, und begert, daz wir im des
                                <expan>uns<ex>er</ex>n</expan>
<expan>offen<ex>en</ex></expan> brief <expan>geb<ex>e</ex>n</expan>
<expan>solt<ex>e</ex>n</expan>, daz er <expan>uns<ex>er</ex></expan>
<expan>b<ex>ur</ex>g<ex>er</ex></expan> ist, <expan>lass<ex>en</ex></expan>
                        wir ew wissen, daz unser gewonheit nicht ist, daz wir
                                <expan>dheine<ex>m</ex></expan>
<expan>uns<ex>er</ex>m</expan>
<expan>b<ex>urger</ex></expan>
<expan>dar<ex>umb</ex></expan>
<expan>offen<ex>en</ex></expan> brief <expan>geb<ex>e</ex>n</expan>; dann ob
                                <expan>d<ex>er</ex></expan>
<expan>eg<ex>enante</ex></expan> ewr sun iht haftes gewünn, wenn das an uns
                        braht würd, so <expan>geb<ex>e</ex>n</expan> wir im
                            <expan>g<ex>er</ex>ne</expan>
<expan>uns<ex>er</ex></expan> fürderbrief als <expan>and<ex>er</ex>n</expan>
<expan>uns<ex>er</ex>n</expan>
<expan>b<ex>ur</ex>g<ex>er</ex>n</expan> und <expan>bitt<ex>e</ex>n</expan>
                        ew, wenn er czeland kum, daz ir in <expan>unt<ex>er</ex>weiset</expan>, daz
                        er bey uns wonhaft sey als <expan>and<ex>er</ex></expan>
<expan>uns<ex>er</ex></expan>
<expan>b<ex>urger</ex></expan>. Und wo wir ew lieb und
                                <expan>frewntsch<ex>aft</ex></expan>
<expan>beweis<ex>en</ex></expan>
<expan>möht<ex>en</ex></expan>, das <expan>tet<ex>e</ex>n</expan> wir
                                <expan>allcz<ex>eit</ex></expan>
<expan>g<ex>er</ex>ne</expan>.</ab>
</div>
